      "answer_id": "granite-vs-parakeet-production-fit",
      "question": "Should Granite Speech 4.1 2B replace Parakeet TDT 0.6b-v3 as the production STT model in brainpowa-realtime-api?",
      "short_title": "Granite vs Parakeet production fit for brainpowa",
      "categories": [
        "stt-evaluation",
        "entity-correction"
      ],
      "answer_methods": [
        "code-experiment",
        "papers",
        "internet"
      ],
      "confidence": "high",
      "created_by_task": "t0014_granite_short_clip_robustness",
      "date_created": "2026-06-30",
      "short_answer": "YES, with a minimum clip duration gate of 2.0 s recommended for the first deployment. Granite Speech\n4.1 2B produces 0% empty output and 0% hallucination across all 44 short clips tested (0.5–3.0 s),\nwhile Parakeet fails on 27.3% of short clips (55.6% empty rate at sub-1 s bins) — directly matching\nthe failure mode that disqualified Whisper from production. On gold-92 (clips 3–13 s), Granite\nachieves 94.8% entity accuracy versus Parakeet's 65.0%, with comparable latency (125–215 ms p50 vs\n32–46 ms); both well within the 800 ms production constraint. Integration effort is low: reading\nbrainpowa-realtime-api base.py confirms the STTAdapter base class already implements\ntranscribe_stream() as accumulate-then-transcribe, so a granite.py adapter only needs to implement\ntranscribe() and model loading — approximately 60–80 lines of Python."
    }
  ]
}
